  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-04 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Thirteen credibility factors are listed; twelve are assessed with achieved levels below required levels. One factor — Equivalency of input parameters — carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' and omits requiredLevel/achievedLevel. The assessment narrative argues this factor 'does not apply because experimental and computational boundary conditions are specified identically in the test protocol,' yet the correct encoding would be 'not-applicable'. At MRL 3 the absence of a formal equivalency assessment materially weakens credibility. Decision: Accepted.",
